Xstrata Says Copper Production to Rise in Second Half

-- B y   M a t t h e w   C r a z e
-- 
2011-07-01T16:48:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/xstrata-says-copper-production-to-rise-in-second-half-correct-.html
(Corrects time period in headline and first paragraph.)  Xstrata Plc (XTA)  said copper production
will increase in the second half of the year and the Zug,
Switzerland-based company can meet its annual output target.  Xstrata and  Anglo American Plc (AAL) ’s Collahuasi copper mine in
Chile is in the process of restarting its port six months after
a ship-loader collapse killed three people, Charlie Sartain,
Xstrata’s head of copper, told reporters in Santiago today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Craze in Santiago at 
